T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 467
EP  - 475
VL  - 36
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper studies the problem of scheduling jobs on parallel machines with setup times. When a machine switches from processing one type of job to another type, setup times are incurred. The problem is to find a feasible schedule for each machine which maximizes the total reward. We study three heuristics for solving this problem. Analytical and empirical results of the heuristics are given.
AB  - This paper studies the problem of scheduling jobs on parallel machines with setup times. When a machine switches from processing one type of job to another type, setup times are incurred. The problem is to find a feasible schedule for each machine which maximizes the total reward. We study three heuristics for solving this problem. Analytical and empirical results of the heuristics are given.
